## 6. Key Conventions

- **async/await** everywhere — FastAPI endpoints and all I/O
- **UUID** for all primary keys (PostgreSQL `uuid_generate_v4()`)
- **Feature flags** via environment variables: `ENABLE_*`, `USE_*` booleans
- **Creator-scoped** — almost every endpoint takes `{creator_id}` path parameter
- **Dual storage** — ToneProfiles in PostgreSQL (primary) + JSON (backup)
- **Logging** — use `logging` module, never `print()` in production
- **Conventional commits** — `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`

## 7. Deploy

```
Railway (Nixpacks) → uvicorn api.main:app
├── API: /dm/*, /copilot/*, /auth/*, etc.
└── SPA: /* → backend/static/index.html
```

- **Build frontend:** `cd frontend && npm run build && cp -r dist/* ../backend/static/`
- **Deploy:** `git push origin main` → Railway auto-deploys
- **Health:** `/health/live`, `/health/ready`
- **Production:** `https://www.clonnectapp.com`

## 8. DM Pipeline

```
Webhook (IG/WA/TG) → DMResponderAgent.process_dm()
  → Pool matching (response_variator_v2)
  → Scout FT v2 via DeepInfra LoRA
  → GPT-4o-mini fallback (via OpenAI)
  → Post-processing (response_fixes, calibration)
  → Step 9b: auto-schedule nurturing (if intent matches)
```

## 9. Development Rules

### Core Principles
- **Small tasks, one at a time.** Never go forward more than one step.
- **Test-Driven Development.** Start with failing tests for any new functionality.
- **Type Safety.** Python: type hints. TypeScript: avoid `any`.
- **Incremental Changes.** Prefer small, focused changes over large modifications.

### Language Standards
- **English Only** for code, comments, logs, docs, git messages, tests, schema
- **Spanish Allowed** only for user-facing UI text

### Git Standards
- Branch naming: `feature/description`, `fix/description`, `refactor/description`
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`
- One logical change per commit. Tests must pass.

